    "claim": "The protocol uses one shared `availableRouters` set for both executable routers and ERC20 spenders (`_gateway`). As a result, every address allowlisted for routing is also permissionlessly eligible to receive token approvals from the proxy.",
    "impact": "Adding a router for call-execution implicitly grants it spender authority over user funds. Any compromised, upgradable, or unexpectedly permissive allowlisted router can be seeded with approvals and then drain proxy-held tokens, even if it was never intended to act as the pull-based gateway.",
    "paths": [
      "Admin allowlists router `R` via `addAvailableRouter`.",
      "A user calls `routerCall` with `_gateway = R` because `R` is in the same shared set.",
      "The proxy approves `R` for the route token.",
      "`R` later uses its spender capability to pull funds from the proxy."
    ]
